HEADWORD: Wolffian
<hw>Wolff"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Discovered, or first described, by Caspar Friedrich
<etsep>Wolff</etsep> (1733-1794), the founder of modern
embryology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Wolffian body</b></col>, <cd>the mesonephros.</cd> --
<col><b>Wolffian duct</b></col>, <cd>the duct from the Wolffian
body.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wolfhound</ent>⟦br⟧
